  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 31,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "A non-Jewish child said to me, 'The houses are yours, but the streets are ours.'",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And after living so many years, and not to be a trace left, that is something.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That's why of all the stories, this one had the greatest impact, because I didn't know that one day I will be an orphan and will starved and tortured.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 32,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But what I remember, at that time, when I asked my mother, 'How could Bontsha endure so much suffering?'",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And my mother, may she rest in peace, answered, in Yiddish, '[YIDDISH]'-- and I'll explain it, what it means in English. '[YIDDISH].",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Sometimes a man is stronger than iron, and other times, weaker than a fly.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 33,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But,' she said, 'we never know our strength till we haven't been tested.'",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
